messages.content: What is the primary functionality of the comfortable UI (ComfyUI)?
ComfyUI is primarily a graphical user interface (GUI) system that utilizes stable diffusion models to generate images and videos.

The specific programming language or framework used for the implementation of ComfyUI is not explicitly mentioned in the document.
How are custom nodes and plugins for ComfyUI created?
Custom nodes and plugins for ComfyUI are created by extending its functionality, as detailed in the 'ComfyUI-Manager' extension.
What are the primary features of the 'ComfyUI-Manager' extension?
The 'ComfyUI-Manager' extension is primarily a workflow and settings manager for ComfyUI.
What is the purpose of the 'ComfyUI-Manager' extension?
The purpose of the 'ComfyUI-Manager' extension is to provide a mechanism for managing workflow settings, workflow flows, as well as string nodes for ComfyUI.
What are the main categories of nodes available in ComfyUI-Manager?
The nodes fall into three main categories: workflow settings, string nodes, and material node colors.
